### Description

When creating a custom form extending a FormGroup, the formGroup directive is broken.

```typescript
interface Hello {
  firstname: FormControl<string | null>;
}

export class HelloForm extends FormGroup<Hello> {
  public constructor() {
    super({
      firstname: new FormControl('Albert'),
    });
  }
}
```

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./app.component.css'],
})
export class AppComponent {
  public form = new HelloForm();
}
```

```html
<div [formGroup]="form"></div>
```

```shell
Error: src/app/app.component.html:1:7 - error TS2322: Type 'HelloForm' is not assignable to type 'FormGroup<any>'.
  Types of property 'controls' are incompatible.
    Type 'Hello' is not assignable to type '{ [key: string]: AbstractControl<any, any>; }'.
      Index signature for type 'string' is missing in type 'Hello'.

1 <div [formGroup]="form"></div>
``` 

